<p style="text-align:justify;">state <span class="DelHand-author">up</span> with his body; <span class="AddHand-author">he had his watch</span> but <span class="DelHand-author">he had</span> no compass.  <span class="AddHand-author">They had all three pocket knives, &amp; tinderboxes with flint &amp; steel.</span>  <span class="DelHand-author">He</span> <span class="AddHand-author">M</span><span class="AddHand-author"><sup>r</sup></span><span class="AddHand-author"> F</span> was very bare of clothes, and in this respect his men were better off than himself.  He had however, <span class="DelHand-author">as</span> a good three point blanket, and his men had also each one.  For some time back they had, in co<span class="AddHand-editors">[n]</span>templation of such an expedition, economised as much as possible in the consumption of the pemican and the <span class="DelHand-author">flour</span> meal that was served out to them, and had laid by all they could from their scanty allowance <span class="DelHand-author">for</span> to form a stock for <span class="DelHand-author">such</span> <span class="AddHand-author">the</span><span class="DelHand-author"><span class="AddHand-author">ir</span></span> journey <span class="AddHand-author">&amp; </span><span class="DelHand-author"><span class="AddHand-author">of</span></span><span class="AddHand-author"> which </span><span class="DelHand-author"><span class="AddHand-author">when they started they had saved</span></span><span class="AddHand-author"> at the time of their departure they calculated would be enough to last them all three for about a fortnight.  They had also one whole dressed orignal-skin, and some pieces, to supply them with shoes or mocassins, together with two or three spare pair of mocassins, and </span><span class="DelHand-author"><span class="AddHand-author">fur</span></span><span class="AddHand-author"> leather mittens, which they did not anticipate were to become part of their stock of eatables.</span></p>
<p class="positiveIndent">The <span class="DelHand-author">Governor</span> <span class="AddHand-author">HB. chief, Williams,</span> being gone as before said; <span class="DelHand-author"><span class="AddHand-author">and</span></span> almost all the men <span class="AddHand-author">being</span> away to their respective departments; and the <span class="DelHand-author"><span class="AddHand-author">Co</span></span><span class="AddHand-author"> Company's</span> schooner <span class="AddHand-author">having</span> sailed to winter at Churchill; they were much less narrowly watched than before <span class="AddHand-author">and their sentinels were discontinued</span>.  Indeed the approach of winter, the severity of which in those parts can not be described <span class="AddHand-author">to,</span> or <span class="DelHand-author">understood</span> <span class="AddHand-author">conceived</span> by, the inhabitants of more genial climates, <span class="DelHand-author">rendered</span> lulled all suspicion of their intention to escape; as every one but those who</p>
<p class="positiveIndent">"groaned under oppression's iron fangs"</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">would have considered such an attempt as one of insanity or of desperation, and <span class="DelHand-author">I</span><span class="AddHand-author">i</span>n fact it partook of both.</p>
